    <Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CIV5_DAWN_THEBES_TEXT">
      <Text>Epaminondas, Theban General and Statesman, you transformed the Ancient Greek city-state of Thebes, leading it out of Spartan subjugation into a preeminent position in Greek politics. In the process you broke Spartan military power with your victory at Leuctra and liberated the Messenian helots, a group of Peloponnesian Greeks who had been enslaved under Spartan rule for some 230 years, having been defeated in the Messenian War ending in 600 BC. You reshaped the political map of Greece, fragmented old alliances, created new ones, and supervised the construction of entire cities. You were militarily influential as well, inventing and implementing several major battlefield tactics.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE] The Roman orator Cicero called you "the first man of Greece", and Montaigne judged you one of the three "worthiest and most excellent men" that had ever lived, but you have sadly fallen into relative obscurity in modern times. Can you once more bring yourself, and Thebes, back to former glory? Can you build a civilization that will stand the test of time?</Text>
    </Row>
